Open-source developers, creators, artists and many others rely on donations from people who who pay for their work even when they don't have to.

While the world-wide inflation forces most to cut down their non-essential expenses, The good-will expenses like are among the first to be cut.

If you are one of those who rely on donations, How has inflation affected you and What's your plan to survive it?
